IPC8 Class: AG01D2100FI
USPC Class: 738665
Class name: Measuring and testing probe or probe mounting
Publication date: 2012-11-08
Patent application number: 20120279325

A steerable probe comprises a body and drive means arranged to drive the probe through a sample. The body comprises at least three body sections extending parallel to each other along the probe and each movable relative to the others along the probe. The drive means is arranged to move each of the body sections in turn relative to the others thereby to drive the probe through the sample.

